{{< figure src="/img/portfolio/little-happies/littlehappies.png" caption="Little Happies at 2016 GaymerX." >}}

### Summary

Little Happies are things that make bring people comfort and happiness in small ways. This includes anything from cute plushies that you might keep by your computer, or a small cupcake in your favorite flavors, or a goofy shirt that you love to wear. Little Happies the game is an over-the-top, bordering on ridiculousness, nod to all the Little Happies out there in the world.  

The game was built with Toni Pizza for the Indiecade Arcade at GaymerX 2014. It is a mod of Ninja Shadow Warrior. We refaced the cabinet, reskinned the game, and added the feature of posting to Twitter (https://twitter.com/iamgamebot) instead of Tumblr. 

### Exhibtions/Demos

-	2016 Indiecade East Showcase: Strange Arcade at the Museum of the Moving Image, NYC [[site](http://www.movingimage.us/exhibitions/2016/04/29/detail/indiecade-east-2016-game-showcase-strange-arcade-2/)]
-	2014, Indiecade Arcade at GaymerX, San Francisco, CA [[site](http://indiecade.tumblr.com/post/91486075198/indiecades-games-at-gaymerx2)]

